Class Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • Parser
  • class Parser
extends java.lang.Object
    A recursive descent parser for the compiler. Each variable has a function associated which calls the other ones according to the action table. If the rule contains terminals, each one of them will me matched.

      • parse

        ParseTree parse()
        Parse the symbols and return the parse tree if there is no syntax error.
        Returns:
        the parse tree created during the parsing

      • Program

        private ParseTree Program()
        Function representing the variable Program. According to the action table, the function will execute a certain rule if the lookahead is corresponding. If the rule contains terminals, there will be a match and the lookahead will be incremented. Otherwise, the function corresponding to the variable is called. Each match return a leaf of the tree. Each function return a recursive tree. Those are stored as children of the tree returned in this function.
        Returns:
        a recursive ParseTree

      • match

        private ParseTree match​(LexicalUnit type)
        Match the input with the lexical unit type. If the match is succesfull, the lookahead is incremented and becomes the next terminal of the input
        Parameters:
        type - lexical unit to be matched
        Returns:
        a leaf of a ParseTree with the matched terminal

        private LexicalUnit lookahead()
        Returns:
